Refactor the following code: apparmor: Replace memcpy + NUL termination with kmemdup_nul in do_setattr.

Refactoring description:
Use kmemdup_nul() to copy 'value' instead of using memcpy() followed by
a manual NUL termination.  No functional changes.

Output the complete corrected function(s).

```c
static int do_setattr(u64 attr, void *value, size_t size)
{
char *command, *largs = NULL, *args = value;
size_t arg_size;
int error;
DEFINE_AUDIT_DATA(ad, LSM_AUDIT_DATA_NONE, AA_CLASS_NONE,
		  OP_SETPROCATTR);

if (size == 0)
	return -EINVAL;

/* AppArmor requires that the buffer must be null terminated atm */
if (args[size - 1] != '\0') {
	/* null terminate */
	largs = args = kmalloc(size + 1, GFP_KERNEL);
	if (!args)
		return -ENOMEM;
	memcpy(args, value, size);
	args[size] = '\0';
}

error = -EINVAL;
